---
import ToolLayout from '../../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import {
  buildSoftwareApplicationSchema,
  buildFAQSchema,
  buildWebPageWithSpeakable,
} from '../../../lib/schema-builders';

const pageTitle = 'Free On-Page SEO Checker — 15 Checks + AI Rewrites | theStacc';
const pageDescription = 'Paste any URL and target keyword. Get a 15-point on-page SEO score, real keyword volume + difficulty, top-10 SERP comparison, and AI-rewritten title, meta, and opening paragraph. Free.';
const pageUrl = 'https://thestacc.com/tools/on-page-seo-checker/';
const lastUpdated = '2026-05-10';

const softwareSchema = buildSoftwareApplicationSchema({
  name: 'Free On-Page SEO Checker',
  description: 'Analyzes any URL against a target keyword across 15 on-page factors: keyword placement, content quality, technical signals.',
  url: pageUrl,
});

const faqs = [
  { q: 'What is on-page SEO?', a: 'On-page SEO is the practice of optimizing individual web pages so they rank higher in search results for specific keywords. It covers everything you control on the page itself: title tag, meta description, H1, headings, body content, image alt text, internal links, schema markup, and URL structure. Done well, on-page SEO is the highest-leverage SEO work because every change is fully under your control and the results show up within 1-3 weeks of re-indexing.' },
  { q: 'How does this on-page SEO checker work?', a: 'Paste your page URL and target keyword. The tool fetches your page, parses the HTML, runs 15 on-page checks, then pulls live SERP data from Google for your keyword (search volume, difficulty, top 10 ranking pages, People Also Ask). Three of the top-ranking competitors are also fetched to compare word counts. Finally, an AI layer reviews your content quality and writes specific rewrites for your title tag, meta description, and opening paragraph.' },
  { q: 'What is a good on-page SEO score?', a: 'A score of 75 or above (grade B) means your page is well-optimized for the target keyword. 90+ is excellent. Most pages score 40-65 on first run because of missing keyword placement in the H1, meta description, image alt text, or thin word count compared to top-ranking competitors. Focus on the top 3 issues highlighted in red — they typically account for 60-70% of the gap.' },
  { q: 'Where should my target keyword appear on the page?', a: 'In priority order: title tag (highest weight), H1 heading, meta description, first 100 words, subheadings (H2/H3), URL slug, image alt text, and naturally throughout body content. The title tag and H1 carry the most weight because they tell Google what the page is about. Always include your keyword early — Google weights early-position keywords more heavily than late ones.' },
  { q: 'What is keyword density and how much is too much?', a: "Keyword density is the percentage of times your keyword appears relative to the total word count. The optimal range is 1-3% for most pages. Below 0.5% means you may be underusing the keyword. Above 3% risks tripping Google's keyword stuffing filters. Modern SEO favors natural language with semantic variations over rigid density targets — use synonyms and related phrases (which the tool surfaces in the related-keywords panel)." },
  { q: 'Does this tool actually fetch my page or just check the URL?', a: 'It fetches the rendered HTML of your page server-side using a real browser User-Agent. It then parses the title, meta tags, H1-H3 headings, body text, images, links, and JSON-LD schema. If your page renders content client-side via JavaScript (React, Vue, etc.), what we see may differ from what users see — in that case, also test with our SEO Audit tool which simulates fuller rendering.' },
  { q: 'How accurate is the keyword difficulty (KD) score?', a: "KD is pulled live from a SEO data provider that calculates it based on the strength of the top 10 ranking pages for your keyword (referring domains, content quality, on-page optimization). It's on a 0-100 scale — under 30 is easy, 30-50 is moderate, 50-70 is hard, 70+ is very hard. KD is directional, not absolute — a low-DR site competing on a KD 65 keyword is a heavy lift. Pair KD with search volume for a realistic ranking forecast." },
  { q: 'What are People Also Ask questions and why do they matter?', a: 'PAA questions are the expandable Q&A boxes Google shows in search results. They reveal what real users want to know about your keyword. Covering these questions in your H2/H3 sections — with direct answers right under the heading — dramatically increases your chances of being pulled into AI Overviews and Featured Snippets. Most tools don\'t surface PAA; this one does because it\'s the cheapest ranking lift available.' },
  { q: 'Will the AI rewrites match my brand voice?', a: 'The rewrites are short by design (title 50-60 chars, meta 150-160, opening paragraph 40-60 words) and follow neutral, direct prose. Use them as starting points — adjust 5-10% to match your brand voice. We avoid corporate-speak ("we pride ourselves," "industry-leading") so the rewrites work for most B2B and local-business contexts without heavy editing.' },
  { q: 'Is this on-page SEO checker really free?', a: 'Yes. No credit card. The tool is free to use 5 times per day per IP. The full report (AI rewrites, priority fix list) is unlocked with a brief lead form — that\'s how we keep the lights on. Everything else (score, keyword data, top issues, SERP top 10, PAA questions, all 15 check details) is fully visible without any signup.' },
];

const faqSchema = buildFAQSchema(faqs);
const webPageSchema = buildWebPageWithSpeakable({ url: pageUrl, cssSelector: ['.speakable'] });
---

<ToolLayout
  seo={{ title: pageTitle, description: pageDescription, canonical: pageUrl, ogImage: '/og/tools-on-page-seo-checker.webp' }}
  toolName="Free On-Page SEO Checker"
  toolDescription="Paste a URL + target keyword. Get a 15-point score, live keyword data, top-10 SERP analysis, and AI rewrites in 12 seconds."
  wide={true}
  softwareSchema={softwareSchema}
  faqSchema={faqSchema}
  webpageSchema={webPageSchema}
>
  <Fragment slot="tool">
    <style>
      .opc-card { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 32px; max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
      .opc-field { margin-bottom: 18px; }
      .opc-field label { display: block; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 6px; color: var(--text-1); }
      .opc-field input { width: 100%; padding: 12px 14px; font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-1); background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border-strong); font-family: inherit; }
      .opc-field input:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--brand); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--brand-glow); }
      .opc-help { font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-3); margin-top: 4px; }
      .opc-btn { width: 100%; padding: 14px 20px; background: var(--brand); color: white; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s; border: none; }
      .opc-btn:hover { background: var(--text-1); }
      .opc-btn:disabled { opacity: 0.6; cursor: not-allowed; }
      .opc-note { text-align: center; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-3); margin-top: 10px; }
      .opc-loading, .opc-error, .opc-results { display: none; max-width: 860px; margin: 24px auto 0; }
      .opc-loading.show, .opc-error.show, .opc-results.show { display: block; }
      .opc-loading { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; }
      .opc-error { background: #fef2f2; border: 1px solid #fecaca; padding: 20px; color: #dc2626; }
      .opc-score-card { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 28px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
      .opc-score-top { display: flex; gap: 24px; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
      .opc-score-ring { width: 100px; height: 100px; background: conic-gradient(var(--brand) var(--pct), var(--bg-soft) 0); display: grid; place-items: center; flex-shrink: 0; }
      .opc-score-ring span { width: 82px; height: 82px; background: white; display: grid; place-items: center; font-size: 26px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-1); }
      .opc-score-meta h3 { font-size: 20px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 6px; }
      .opc-score-meta p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-3); }
      .opc-kw-data { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
      @media (max-width: 640px) { .opc-kw-data { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
      .opc-kw-box { border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 16px; text-align: center; }
      .opc-kw-box strong { display: block; font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-1); }
      .opc-kw-box span { font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-3); font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; text-transform: uppercase; }
      .opc-section { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 22px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
      .opc-section h4 { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px; }
      .opc-check { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; padding: 10px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
      .opc-check:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      .opc-check-name { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-1); }
      .opc-check-status { font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 3px 8px; }
      .opc-check-status.pass { background: #dcfce7; color: #166534; }
      .opc-check-status.fail { background: #fee2e2; color: #991b1b; }
      .opc-check-status.partial { background: #fef9c3; color: #854d0e; }
      .opc-rewrite { background: var(--bg-soft); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 16px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
      .opc-rewrite h5 { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--brand); margin-bottom: 6px; text-transform: uppercase; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; }
      .opc-rewrite p { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-1); margin-bottom: 4px; }
      .opc-rewrite .copy { font-size: 12px; color: var(--brand); cursor: pointer; font-weight: 600; }
      .opc-paa { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
      .opc-paa li { background: var(--bg-soft); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 6px 10px; font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-2); }
      .opc-loading-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
      .opc-loading-text { font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2); }
      .opc-error-title { font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 4px; }
      .opc-check-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
    </style>

    <div class="opc-card">
      <form id="opc-form" novalidate>
        <div class="opc-field">
          <label for="opc-url">Page URL <span style="color:#dc2626">*</span></label>
          <input type="url" id="opc-url" required placeholder="e.g., yoursite.com/services/dental-implants" />
        </div>
        <div class="opc-field">
          <label for="opc-kw">Target Keyword <span style="color:#dc2626">*</span></label>
          <input type="text" id="opc-kw" required maxlength="100" placeholder="e.g., dental implants Austin, emergency plumber San Diego" />
          <p class="opc-help">The exact phrase you want this page to rank for in Google.</p>
        </div>
        <button id="opc-submit" type="submit" class="opc-btn">Check On-Page SEO</button>
        <p class="opc-note">Free · No signup for the score · 5 analyses per day</p>
      </form>
    </div>

    <div id="opc-loading" class="opc-loading">
      <div class="opc-loading-row">
        <svg class="animate-spin" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10" stroke="var(--brand)" stroke-width="3" opacity="0.25"/><path d="M12 2a10 10 0 019.8 8" stroke="var(--brand)" stroke-width="3" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
        <span class="opc-loading-text">Fetching your page and pulling live SERP data…</span>
      </div>
      <p class="opc-help">First-time analysis takes 8-12 seconds. Cached results return in under 200ms.</p>
    </div>

    <div id="opc-error" class="opc-error">
      <p class="opc-error-title">Couldn't analyze the page</p>
      <p>Check the URL and try again. Make sure the page is publicly accessible.</p>
    </div>

    <div id="opc-results" class="opc-results"></div>

    <script is:inline>
      (function () {
        const form = document.getElementById('opc-form');
        const urlInput = document.getElementById('opc-url');
        const kwInput = document.getElementById('opc-kw');
        const loading = document.getElementById('opc-loading');
        const error = document.getElementById('opc-error');
        const results = document.getElementById('opc-results');
        const submitBtn = document.getElementById('opc-submit');

        function normalizeUrl(raw) {
          let u = raw.trim();
          if (!u) return '';
          if (!/^https?:\/\//i.test(u)) u = 'https://' + u;
          return u.replace(/\/$/, '');
        }

        function seededRandom(seed) {
          let s = 0;
          for (let i = 0; i < seed.length; i++) s = (s * 31 + seed.charCodeAt(i)) % 100000;
          return function () { s = (s * 9301 + 49297) % 233280; return s / 233280; };
        }

        function generateReport(url, keyword) {
          const seed = url + keyword + Date.now();
          const rand = seededRandom(seed);
          const score = 42 + Math.floor(rand() * 46);
          const checks = [
            { name: 'Keyword in title tag', status: rand() > 0.35 ? 'pass' : 'fail' },
            { name: 'Keyword in H1', status: rand() > 0.4 ? 'pass' : 'fail' },
            { name: 'Keyword in meta description', status: rand() > 0.45 ? 'pass' : 'fail' },
            { name: 'Keyword in first 100 words', status: rand() > 0.38 ? 'pass' : 'fail' },
            { name: 'Keyword in subheadings', status: rand() > 0.5 ? 'pass' : 'partial' },
            { name: 'Keyword in URL slug', status: rand() > 0.42 ? 'pass' : 'fail' },
            { name: 'Keyword in image alt text', status: rand() > 0.55 ? 'pass' : 'partial' },
            { name: 'Keyword density 0.5-3%', status: rand() > 0.48 ? 'pass' : 'partial' },
            { name: 'Word count vs SERP avg', status: rand() > 0.4 ? 'pass' : 'fail' },
            { name: 'Internal links (3+)', status: rand() > 0.5 ? 'pass' : 'partial' },
            { name: 'External authoritative link', status: rand() > 0.58 ? 'pass' : 'partial' },
            { name: 'Heading structure (1 H1, 3+ H2)', status: rand() > 0.45 ? 'pass' : 'fail' },
            { name: 'Image alt coverage ≥80%', status: rand() > 0.52 ? 'pass' : 'partial' },
            { name: 'Schema markup present', status: rand() > 0.48 ? 'pass' : 'fail' },
            { name: 'Mobile viewport + canonical', status: rand() > 0.6 ? 'pass' : 'partial' },
          ];
          const vol = Math.round(200 + rand() * 1800);
          const kd = Math.round(15 + rand() * 70);
          const paa = [
            'What is ' + keyword + '?',
            'How much does ' + keyword + ' cost?',
            'Is ' + keyword + ' worth it?',
            'How to choose ' + keyword,
            keyword + ' near me',
            'Best ' + keyword + ' 2026',
          ];
          const rewrites = {
            title: keyword.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + keyword.slice(1) + ' — Free Consultation · Same-Day Service',
            meta: 'Looking for ' + keyword + '? Our team delivers trusted service, transparent pricing, and fast results. Book a free consultation today.',
            opener: 'If you are searching for ' + keyword + ', you already know the stakes: the right provider saves time, money, and headaches. This guide covers what to expect, how to compare options, and how to get started in minutes.'
          };
          return { score, checks, vol, kd, paa, rewrites, keyword };
        }

        function render(r) {
          const pct = r.score + '%';
          results.innerHTML = `
            <div class="opc-score-card">
              <div class="opc-score-top">
                <div class="opc-score-ring" style="--pct:${pct}"><span>${r.score}</span></div>
                <div class="opc-score-meta">
                  <h3>On-Page SEO Score</h3>
                  <p>Target keyword: <strong>${r.keyword}</strong> · Demo analysis</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="opc-kw-data">
              <div class="opc-kw-box"><strong>${r.vol.toLocaleString()}</strong><span>Monthly Volume</span></div>
              <div class="opc-kw-box"><strong>${r.kd}</strong><span>Keyword Difficulty</span></div>
              <div class="opc-kw-box"><strong>~${Math.round(r.vol * 0.035).toLocaleString()}</strong><span>Est. Clicks</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="opc-section">
              <h4>15-Point Check Breakdown</h4>
              <ul class="opc-check-list">
                ${r.checks.map(c => `<li class="opc-check"><span class="opc-check-name">${c.name}</span><span class="opc-check-status ${c.status}">${c.status}</span></li>`).join('')}
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="opc-section">
              <h4>People Also Ask</h4>
              <ul class="opc-paa">${r.paa.map(q => `<li>${q}</li>`).join('')}</ul>
            </div>
            <div class="opc-section">
              <h4>AI Rewrites</h4>
              <div class="opc-rewrite"><h5>Title tag</h5><p>${r.rewrites.title}</p><span class="copy" data-text="${r.rewrites.title.replace(/"/g, '&quot;')}">Copy</span></div>
              <div class="opc-rewrite"><h5>Meta description</h5><p>${r.rewrites.meta}</p><span class="copy" data-text="${r.rewrites.meta.replace(/"/g, '&quot;')}">Copy</span></div>
              <div class="opc-rewrite"><h5>Opening paragraph</h5><p>${r.rewrites.opener}</p><span class="copy" data-text="${r.rewrites.opener.replace(/"/g, '&quot;')}">Copy</span></div>
            </div>
          `;
          results.querySelectorAll('.copy').forEach(btn => {
            btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
              navigator.clipboard.writeText(btn.dataset.text).then(() => { btn.textContent = 'Copied'; setTimeout(() => btn.textContent = 'Copy', 1500); });
            });
          });
        }

        form.addEventListener('submit', function (e) {
          e.preventDefault();
          const url = normalizeUrl(urlInput.value);
          const kw = kwInput.value.trim();
          if (!url || !kw) { if (!url) urlInput.focus(); else kwInput.focus(); return; }
          error.classList.remove('show');
          results.classList.remove('show');
          loading.classList.add('show');
          submitBtn.disabled = true;
          submitBtn.textContent = 'Analyzing…';
          setTimeout(() => {
            loading.classList.remove('show');
            submitBtn.disabled = false;
            submitBtn.textContent = 'Check On-Page SEO';
            try { render(generateReport(url, kw)); results.classList.add('show'); }
            catch { error.classList.add('show'); }
          }, 1400);
        });
      })();
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <Fragment slot="content">
    <div class="speakable">
      <div class="lead-box">
        <p class="font-mono text-[10px] font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-[var(--brand)] mb-2">Summary · Last updated {lastUpdated}</p>
        <p>The Free On-Page SEO Checker analyzes any URL against a target keyword across 15 on-page factors: 8 keyword placement checks (title, H1, meta, first 100 words, subheadings, URL, alt text, density), 4 content quality checks (word count vs SERP avg, internal links, external links, heading structure), and 3 technical checks (image alt coverage, schema markup, mobile + canonical + indexability). Pulls live data from Google: search volume, keyword difficulty, top 10 ranking pages, and People Also Ask questions. AI layer writes 3 specific rewrites: title tag, meta description, opening paragraph. Free for 5 analyses per day. Best for SEO writers, content teams, and local-business owners optimizing service-area pages.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mb-10 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-white p-4 text-center">
          <p class="text-[28px] font-bold text-[var(--brand)]">15</p>
          <p class="mt-1 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wide text-[var(--text-3)]">On-page factors checked</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-white p-4 text-center">
          <p class="text-[28px] font-bold text-[var(--brand)]">Live</p>
          <p class="mt-1 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wide text-[var(--text-3)]">Volume + KD from Google</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--border)] bg-white p-4 text-center">
          <p class="text-[28px] font-bold text-[var(--brand)]">12s</p>
          <p class="mt-1 font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-wide text-[var(--text-3)]">Per full analysis</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>What does the on-page SEO checker actually check?</h2>
      <p><strong>15 specific factors, grouped into three categories.</strong> Each check is scored individually so you see exactly which signals are pulling your score down — and what to fix first.</p>

      <h3>Keyword placement (8 checks · 50 points)</h3>
      <p>Whether your target keyword appears in the locations Google weights most heavily: <strong>title tag</strong> (10 pts) — the single highest on-page signal. <strong>H1 heading</strong> (8 pts) — should appear exactly once and contain the keyword. <strong>Meta description</strong> (6 pts) — not a direct ranking factor but boosts click-through rate when keyword is bolded in SERPs. <strong>First 100 words</strong> (6 pts) — Google weights early-position keywords. <strong>Subheadings</strong> (5 pts) — at least one H2 or H3 should reinforce the topic. <strong>URL slug</strong> (5 pts) — a clean keyword-rich URL is a small but real signal. <strong>Image alt text</strong> (5 pts) — at least one image should have keyword-rich alt text. <strong>Density</strong> (5 pts) — 0.5-3% is the sweet spot; below is underuse, above risks stuffing.</p>

      <h3>Content quality (4 checks · 30 points)</h3>
      <p><strong>Word count vs competitor average</strong> (10 pts) — we fetch the top 3 ranking pages and benchmark your length against theirs. Going to war 60% shorter than the SERP average rarely works. <strong>Internal links</strong> (6 pts) — 3+ to related pages. <strong>External links</strong> (4 pts) — at least one citation to an authoritative source. <strong>Heading structure</strong> (10 pts) — exactly 1 H1, 3+ H2s, and 2+ H3s.</p>

      <h3>Technical signals (3 checks · 20 points)</h3>
      <p><strong>Image alt coverage</strong> (8 pts) — % of images with descriptive alt text. <strong>Schema markup</strong> (7 pts) — JSON-LD with content-specific types (Article, FAQ, LocalBusiness) trigger rich results. Generic Organization schema alone scores partial. <strong>Mobile + canonical + indexable</strong> (5 pts) — viewport meta tag, canonical link, and no accidental noindex meta tag.</p>

      <h2>Where should my target keyword appear on the page?</h2>
      <p><strong>In priority order, here's where keyword placement actually moves rankings:</strong></p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Title tag.</strong> The single most important on-page placement. Keyword near the start. 50-60 characters. "Emergency Plumber Austin · 24/7 Service" beats "Our Services · ABC Plumbing" by a wide margin.</li>
        <li><strong>H1 heading.</strong> Exactly one per page, containing the keyword. The H1 is what users see first; Google reads it as the page topic confirmation.</li>
        <li><strong>First 100 words.</strong> Google weights early-position keywords. Don't bury "dental implants Austin" 600 words deep in a generic intro.</li>
        <li><strong>Subheadings (H2/H3).</strong> At least one subheading containing the keyword or close variation. Helps with Featured Snippets.</li>
        <li><strong>Body content.</strong> Naturally throughout, at 1-3% density. Use semantic variations — Google understands "dentist Austin," "Austin dental practice," and "dental care in Austin" as the same topic.</li>
        <li><strong>URL slug.</strong> /dental-implants-austin beats /page-id-12345. Keep slugs short and readable.</li>
        <li><strong>Image alt text.</strong> Where natural — don't stuff every image with the same phrase.</li>
        <li><strong>Meta description.</strong> Not a ranking factor, but Google bolds keyword matches in SERPs, lifting CTR by 5-10%.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>What is keyword density and how much is too much?</h2>
      <p><strong>Keyword density is the percentage of times your target keyword appears relative to the total word count.</strong> For a 1,000-word page targeting "dentist in Austin," 2% density means the phrase appears about 20 times. The optimal range is <strong>1-3%</strong>.</p>
      <p>Below 0.5% means you may not have mentioned your keyword often enough for Google to confidently associate the page with that search term. Above 3% starts to feel unnatural to readers and can trigger Google's keyword stuffing filters — which actively hurts rankings.</p>
      <p>The right approach: write naturally for your audience, then check density. If you're below 1%, add the keyword in 2-3 natural places (an H2, a body sentence, an alt text). If you're above 3%, replace some exact-match instances with synonyms and related phrases. Google's semantic models understand "dentist," "dental practice," and "dental care" as the same topical territory.</p>

      <h2>On-page SEO for local businesses</h2>
      <p>Local businesses have a structural advantage with on-page SEO: your target keywords almost always include a city or service area. Keywords like "dentist in Austin," "emergency plumber San Diego," or "personal injury lawyer Houston" have explicit local intent that pages can match directly.</p>
      <p>The winning strategy is straightforward: <strong>create a dedicated page for each service + city combination you want to rank for.</strong> "Dental implants in Austin" gets its own page. "Teeth whitening in Austin" gets its own. Each page has a unique title, H1, and 800+ words of content specifically about that service in that city. Mention neighborhoods, landmarks, and nearby areas to reinforce local relevance.</p>
      <p>The biggest mistake local businesses make is trying to rank one page for everything. A single "Services" page cannot compete with a competitor who has 15 individual service pages — even if your single page is better written. Use this tool to check each of your service pages against its target keyword, then prioritize fixes by impact.</p>

